      "Updated Step-by-Step Procedure to include verification with Drill Pipe Performance Data Sheet"
    ],
    "summary": "On November 13, 2021, during abandonment operations at Green Canyon Block 518, a 4.5-inch double drill pipe assembly weighing approximately 1,500 pounds unexpectedly came free from the drill pipe elevators and fell approximately one foot onto the rotary deck, coming to rest against the lower belly fingerboard. The incident occurred because incorrect elevator inserts (4.5-inch EU \u2013 5-inch IEU) were installed instead of the required inserts (4-inch EU \u2013 4.5-inch IEU) specified in the rental drill pipe performance data sheet. No injuries were reported, but the incident had high severity dropped object potential.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Updated Step-by-Step Procedure to include 'Change Inserts in Elevators' with verification against appropriate Drill Pipe Performance Data Sheet"
    ],
    "key_phrases": [
      "dropped object",
      "elevator inserts",
      "incorrect size",
      "rental drill pipe",
      "human error",
      "positive confirmation",
      "performance data sheet"
    ]
  },
